Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.44,0:00:06.90,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Serara, the girl we saved in Susukino,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.28,0:00:10.43,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,belongs to Marielle's guild, \Nthe Crescent Moon Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.66,0:00:15.65,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,A guild is a team comprised of many players.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.12,0:00:19.52,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Guilds offer many advantages that parties,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.52,0:00:22.38,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,which are more provisional, don't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.25,0:00:26.07,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,For example, a shared vault in the game's bank,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.07,0:00:28.57,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and a dedicated communication system.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.57,0:00:32.18,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And most important, potential use of a guild hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.18,0:00:35.13,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,located here, at the Guild Building.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.95,0:00:41.14,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,These halls can be purchased or rented, \Nand are divided into several ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.56,0:00:46.15,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, you select a hall \Nbased on your guild's size.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.87,0:00:51.42,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Crescent Moon Alliance uses what's known \Nas a rank-B hall, consisting of seven rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.05,0:00:58.04,SignA,S,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home, Serara!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.48,0:00:56.16,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,For them, the size is exactly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.07,0:02:34.15,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Making the food without using \Ncommands is more difficult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.15,0:02:36.15,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,but it's worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.68,0:02:39.55,Default,Cook,0000,0000,0000,,This smell... This perfectly charred color...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.55,0:02:41.18,Default,Cook,0000,0000,0000,,I remember this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.18,0:02:43.41,Default,Cook,0000,0000,0000,,It's food!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.41,0:02:46.17,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to make it too salty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.26,0:02:49.31,Default,Cook,0000,0000,0000,,I still can't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.31,0:02:54.02,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,To make difficult foods, \Nyou need a high cooking skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.54,0:02:58.65,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,And even if two people with the same \Nlevel use the same ingredients,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.65,0:03:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,their dishes can still taste different.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.38,0:03:04.39,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,It's no different than in our old world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.30,0:03:07.25,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Serara's working hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.25,0:03:10.79,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Even though this party is for her...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.87,0:03:16.80,Title1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1322,1)}Resolve
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.46,0:03:15.46,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.83,0:03:20.46,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.46,0:03:24.61,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Your level isn't what's important. \NIt's what comes after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.61,0:03:26.08,Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,What comes after my level?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.08,0:03:27.52,Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Secret techniques?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.52,0:03:30.48,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I mean panties.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.48,0:03:31.35,Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Pa—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.35,0:03:33.48,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.74,0:03:35.77,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing much, just p—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.77,0:03:38.32,Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Powerful monsters! About powerful monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.11,0:03:40.18,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Marielle?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.60,0:03:41.68,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.37,0:03:45.68,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.68,0:03:49.24,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,We shouldn't let our rivals learn \Nabout this food for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.45,0:03:52.17,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Why? It's a big deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.17,0:03:53.75,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It's too big a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.27,0:03:58.00,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,If people suddenly find out, \Nit could cause problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.28,0:03:59.67,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Shiroe said.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.14,0:04:02.95,Default,Miko,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.95,0:04:04.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I-It was nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.49,0:04:06.21,Default,Ears,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's grateful!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.21,0:04:07.90,Default,Ears,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have a toast!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.31,0:04:14.91,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.91,0:04:17.18,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Not just Ashlin, but Akatsuki, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.18,0:04:19.06,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.06,0:04:20.10,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Ashlin...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.10,0:04:21.38,Default,As,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.38,0:04:24.91,Default,As,0000,0000,0000,,Today, we have three types \Nof summer dress for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.36,0:04:27.51,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I am my lord's personal ninja!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.51,0:04:29.37,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't wear such frivolous things!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.68,0:04:32.37,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe's given his permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.65,0:04:34.81,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Now, just give up...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.81,0:04:38.25,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You sold me out, my lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.25,0:04:40.82,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You sold me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.34,0:04:50.97,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Marie, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.09,0:04:57.26,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have a lot of cleaning tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.87,0:04:59.56,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to sleep, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.56,0:05:00.73,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not that tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.98,0:05:03.39,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Then shall I make some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.67,0:05:07.87,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You really helped us this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.19,0:05:09.46,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.46,0:05:11.01,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.41,0:05:13.79,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do anything too big.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.79,0:05:18.63,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,If it wasn't big, then what would be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.63,0:05:20.92,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,While I was away, what's happened here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.92,0:05:23.34,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Here? You mean in Akihabara?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.60,0:05:28.59,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's better than it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.10,0:05:32.85,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,There is far less PKing, and it's a little safer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.33,0:05:34.10,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.63,0:05:38.61,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't say exactly why, but there's \Nsomething unpleasant in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.39,0:05:43.99,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's like, well... Like everyone \Nhas fallen into ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.99,0:05:45.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Ranks?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.70,0:05:49.40,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,We're a small guild, with fewer \Nthan thirty members, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.40,0:05:53.37,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,We have four level 90s, \Nwhile most are under 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.88,0:05:55.71,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But the biggest guilds...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.24,0:06:00.38,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,For example, have you heard \Nof D.D.D., Crusty's guild?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.34,0:06:05.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The raid guild that beat Oracle's Tower, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.70,0:06:10.04,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Legion Raid that they said the \NJapanese couldn't have beaten...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.57,0:06:11.51,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.22,0:06:16.14,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,A raid like that can have hundred-player fights.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.90,0:06:21.91,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly, they have over 1,500 members, \Nincluding plenty of level 90s.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.91,0:06:24.02,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Then, by "rank," you meant the guilds?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.35,0:06:25.71,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It feels as though
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.71,0:06:29.68,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,the bigger guilds are determining \Nthe town's feel and its rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.22,0:06:33.31,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,For example, who has priority using the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.31,0:06:34.54,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.37,0:06:37.04,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same way with the hunting grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.71,0:06:40.21,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Since the strong and weak guilds were divided,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.21,0:06:44.27,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,the weak guilds will no longer approach \Nthe stronger guilds' territories.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.07,0:06:50.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Then the larger guilds have \Ntaken all the good hunting spots?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.77,0:06:53.68,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You can't fight in the town, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.22,0:06:58.52,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't mean you can \Nclash in the hunting areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.52,0:07:04.50,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it means there's less PKing, which is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.50,0:07:06.03,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But that's still...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.37,0:07:09.10,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow, I don't like it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.10,0:07:11.28,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I understand what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.63,0:07:13.21,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't just the hunting grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.94,0:07:17.29,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Invisible barriers are being erected everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.78,0:07:21.69,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I think that's what they mean \Nby the guilds falling into ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.05,0:07:24.98,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No one's to blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.60,0:07:28.55,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm sure the large guilds \Nhave their own problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.21,0:07:32.52,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No laws or ethics prohibit people from \Nusing whatever strategy they can
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.52,0:07:35.35,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,to give themselves an edge in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.97,0:07:38.10,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.55,0:07:41.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.15,0:07:47.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Though perhaps it's a matter of preference.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.56,0:07:49.49,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.13,0:07:52.74,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,A few days ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.53,0:07:58.38,Default - flashback,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,But even if we try to oppose the bigger guilds...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.38,0:08:01.83,Default - flashback,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we're trying to think of a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.16,0:08:05.75,Default - flashback,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,For example, we could share the \Nhunting grounds among ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.47,0:08:09.13,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,...many small guilds that know each other well
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.13,0:08:12.51,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,discussed the possibility of \Ncreating a joint council.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.17,0:08:18.06,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But each of the small guilds has its own opinions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.59,0:08:23.06,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,We ended up quarreling over minor \Ndifferences of opinion and selfish requests...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.69,0:08:25.06,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.49,0:08:29.23,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we talk about this a bit more?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.23,0:08:31.54,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.54,0:08:33.05,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.04,0:08:35.74,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.74,0:08:38.31,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to help, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.31,0:08:41.45,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I knew this wouldn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.16,0:08:44.25,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Further,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.64,0:08:48.99,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,the Black Sword Knights and the \NSilver Sword are aiming for 91.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.99,0:08:50.26,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,91?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.85,0:08:55.38,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The old level cap was 90, \Nbut with the expansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.38,0:08:56.26,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.07,0:09:02.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,With The Novasphere Pioneers expansion, \Nthe level cap was raised to 100,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.63,0:09:03.53,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.33,0:09:09.16,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,And since no new players have \Nentered since the Apocalypse...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.16,0:09:11.02,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.02,0:09:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the limit on how \Nmany you can allow to join...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.32,0:09:18.28,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The Black Sword Knights have always \Nhad a thing about being the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.78,0:09:23.29,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Their guild master, Isaac, is proud... \NOr maybe just enjoys excluding others...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.29,0:09:27.17,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,He won't allow anyone below 85 to join.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.94,0:09:34.82,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,So he isn't in the position D.D.D. was, \Nwhere he can just start absorbing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.82,0:09:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a bunch of smaller guilds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.94,0:09:40.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,He's trying to fight quantity with quality, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.78,0:09:41.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.63,0:09:46.27,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,At a bare minimum, they'd need \Nto hunt for level-85 monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.04,0:09:49.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But this isn't the same as the game...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.68,0:09:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that pretty dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.52,0:09:55.19,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It would be if they did it the normal way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.07,0:10:00.45,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,They're using EXP pots.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.87,0:10:03.04,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,EXP pots?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.35,0:10:07.54,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mean they're leveling up by cheating?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.24,0:10:10.96,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,EXP pots...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.63,0:10:15.96,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Items that slightly increase attack \Npower and health regeneration.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.61,0:10:21.39,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And they double experience earned from combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.10,0:10:19.65,SignD,S,0000,0000,0000,,Death
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.19,0:10:25.45,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,One of these potions
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.45,0:10:30.35,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,was freely distributed to every \Nplayer below level 30 once a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.35,0:10:36.05,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,so new players could level up and \Nstart enjoying the game more quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.38,0:10:39.88,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,After the Apocalypse,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.88,0:10:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a guild called Hamelin gathered new players, \Nclaiming they wanted to help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.96,0:10:49.29,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But they're selling their EXP pots
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.29,0:10:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to large guilds that want to raise their levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.43,0:11:02.81,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's all starting to go wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.40,0:11:06.40,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,This town... This world...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.73,0:11:09.06,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Who's at fault?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.23,0:11:14.22,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, to a greater or lesser degree, everyone is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.39,0:11:17.62,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Including me, since I'm not doing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.02,0:11:21.07,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.77,0:11:23.57,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I only went to Susukino
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.99,0:11:27.88,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,to vent some of my frustration \Nat the way things are going.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.82,0:11:30.80,Default - italics,?,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.09,0:11:34.08,Default - italics,?,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing wrong with thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.92,0:11:40.29,Default - italics,?,0000,0000,0000,,But you're smart enough, so why \Nnot just solve the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.38,0:11:46.77,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But what can I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.34,0:11:49.67,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even have a guild...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.90,0:11:54.10,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a guild...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.70,0:11:55.61,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.98,0:11:58.57,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Tohya \N{\fs18}Hamelin\N\N{\fs22}Minori\N{\fs18}Hamelin \N\N{\fs22}Shigeru\N{\fs18}Honesty \N\N{\fs22}Crusty\N{\fs18}D.D.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.97,0:12:01.70,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's just an excuse to run away...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.23,0:12:07.68,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,Can't sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.45,0:12:09.33,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.33,0:12:11.91,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm too tired to sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.32,0:12:17.10,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,Your brother helped me out yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.99,0:12:19.34,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya did?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.34,0:12:21.40,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,He's a good guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.40,0:12:24.04,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,Kind, cheerful, and hard-working.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.04,0:12:25.72,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,He's just empty-headed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.37,0:12:30.07,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,You two seem to really get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.66,0:12:32.85,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,When this world was still a game,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.34,0:12:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you two would form a party and \Nadventure together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.78,0:12:37.86,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.63,0:12:39.93,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.57,0:12:42.94,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya wanted to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:47.37,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,All the old guilds that invited me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.80,0:12:51.70,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,just wanted to take advantage of \Nmy status as a veteran player.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.06,0:12:54.95,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I hated it, and that's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.59,0:12:56.88,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, that isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.64,0:13:01.48,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't all bad, having people rely on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.08,0:13:05.69,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,I wish our guild master had \Na better grasp of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.69,0:13:08.51,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Our guild's done for...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.59,0:13:12.04,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But when a lot of people get together,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.04,0:13:15.52,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,lip service isn't enough to get \Nby anymore. And I hated that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.94,0:13:18.02,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.66,0:13:21.32,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I knew all that going in...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.78,0:13:26.61,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,A guild... A guild?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.61,0:13:30.28,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Do you still not like guilds, Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.74,0:13:32.79,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Chief...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.45,0:13:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.21,0:13:40.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I don't really know anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.84,0:13:44.21,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The more I think about why I didn't like guilds,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.21,0:13:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the more haughty and childish I seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.26,0:13:53.34,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that the system itself \Nmakes it easy for guilds to go rotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.34,0:13:58.54,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,So I can understand why you'd want \Nto keep your distance from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.77,0:14:05.52,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,But if there were a thing that never went \Nbad, I don't know that I'd trust it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.47,0:14:11.38,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Any kind of life can go wrong, or sicken, or suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.38,0:14:14.51,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Lives get old, decay, and finally die.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.20,0:14:21.09,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Disliking that fact because it hurts isn't \Nany different than disliking life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.84,0:14:25.31,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,I know you realize this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.31,0:14:27.24,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,For example, our old place,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.24,0:14:30.93,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,the Tea Party, was a wonderful place...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.59,0:14:37.06,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,But the reason was because everyone \Nworked to make it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.97,0:14:43.23,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Any treasure you attain without anyone \Never working is no treasure at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.16,0:14:47.36,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.35,0:14:50.86,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Tea Party and the Crescent Moon Alliance...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.04,0:14:55.12,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,In both, there was someone hard \Nat work behind the scenes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.66,0:15:00.50,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Chief, what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.50,0:15:03.55,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,The most amazing thing that you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.28,0:15:05.85,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.85,0:15:08.55,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,You hold back too often.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.85,0:15:13.86,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you need to feel \Nso bound by duty all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.73,0:15:17.11,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, there's no need to hold back!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.81,0:15:21.70,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I've kept you waiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.70,0:15:23.20,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.20,0:15:25.91,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Both of you were waiting for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.48,0:15:27.94,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.81,0:15:33.35,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of going elsewhere, \Nyou stayed with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.87,0:15:35.31,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.37,0:15:47.21,Default - italics,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, a message...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.71,0:15:54.47,HUD1,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.45,0:15:51.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Um, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.63,0:15:52.75,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.31,0:15:54.47,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.92,0:15:57.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,This is Minori, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.82,0:16:00.97,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.75,0:16:04.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Listen carefully, Minori...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.26,0:16:07.68,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Cough softly once for yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.17,0:16:09.53,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Twice for no.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.09,0:16:12.82,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Three times if you want to say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.28,0:16:14.82,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.82,0:16:20.29,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe knows what's happening to us now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.29,0:16:22.62,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Cough once if you understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:28.36,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're both in Hamelin, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.12,0:16:34.42,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And you're giving your EXP pots to Hamelin?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.69,0:16:38.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.59,0:16:43.95,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.76,0:16:49.99,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.87,0:16:58.41,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You want to say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.30,0:17:04.67,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I did tell you to cough three times \Nif you had something to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.64,0:17:08.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'll hurry, so I can hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.07,0:17:12.68,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,For now, I'll believe you're okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.68,0:17:15.29,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,So believe in me, too, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.82,0:17:17.55,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come to rescue you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.55,0:17:19.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.18,0:17:32.50,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Shiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.50,0:17:34.77,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord, don't worry me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.77,0:17:36.79,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,If you're leaving, say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.79,0:17:38.16,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.16,0:17:39.51,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.67,0:17:43.65,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.25,0:17:46.17,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Those two have been waiting
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.82,0:17:49.34,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,for my words.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.09,0:17:58.72,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,This time, I'd like your help with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.02,0:18:00.68,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Our help?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.68,0:18:03.43,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Anything you need, Shiroe!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.95,0:18:05.99,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.99,0:18:09.21,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The Crescent Moon Alliance owes you much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.21,0:18:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.61,0:18:14.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Some twins I know are being held captive...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.30,0:18:17.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, being forced to stay in a nasty guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.01,0:18:21.12,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to save them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.43,0:18:22.83,Default,As,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.83,0:18:25.70,Default,As,0000,0000,0000,,So you just need them to quit the guild, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.70,0:18:27.85,Default,As,0000,0000,0000,,We could draw them off...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.85,0:18:28.67,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.39,0:18:31.42,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,This guild you're talking about...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.42,0:18:37.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,This guild supposedly gathers new \Nplayers and takes their EXP pots.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.85,0:18:40.07,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Hamelin...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.08,0:18:45.02,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's time they left.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.51,0:18:50.83,Default,As,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.83,0:18:52.90,Default,As,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mean you'll destroy them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.56,0:18:56.44,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, I mean exactly what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.16,0:19:00.45,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to have them leave Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.48,0:19:06.13,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro, I understand how you feel...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.13,0:19:07.35,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But we...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.35,0:19:10.01,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but please let me finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.46,0:19:12.46,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,This is only the first part.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.57,0:19:16.80,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Hamelin's just a small portion of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.33,0:19:24.40,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I don't really like the \Nway Akihabara feels right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.16,0:19:27.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's petty, pathetic, and cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.29,0:19:29.06,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's why
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.99,0:19:32.02,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to clean the place up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.86,0:19:36.47,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Akihabara is our hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.47,0:19:38.86,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's the largest city on the Japanese server.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.57,0:19:44.16,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And it's sad, unpleasant, frail...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.72,0:19:47.41,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,474)}Everyone walks with their heads down...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.00,0:19:53.42,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if our only purpose in \Nlife were to be pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.37,0:19:57.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We number thirty thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.49,0:19:59.92,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But that also means there are \Nonly thirty thousand of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.81,0:20:06.43,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I think everyone's been underestimating \Nthis world far too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.84,0:20:09.93,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't nearly desperate enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.15,0:20:15.39,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.11,0:20:19.94,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Please help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.74,0:20:22.41,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.12,0:20:24.31,Default,As,0000,0000,0000,,Guild master...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.19,0:20:27.50,Default,As,0000,0000,0000,,Could we at least hear him out?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.29,0:20:32.75,Default,As,0000,0000,0000,,For a long time, I've been feeling the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.16,0:20:34.49,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Shouryuu...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.49,0:20:36.89,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,How would you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.89,0:20:38.46,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It depends on your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.46,0:20:39.76,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.41,0:20:44.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we'll decide if it's something \Nwe can help you with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.22,0:20:48.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I need money.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.49,0:20:50.77,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,For now,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.62,0:20:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,five million gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.42,0:20:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,F-Five million...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.08,0:20:58.77,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,M-Money?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.15,0:21:00.41,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,That's insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.41,0:21:02.15,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Our treasury only has sixty thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.15,0:21:04.51,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we included all our members' belongings...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.51,0:21:07.16,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What would you use all that money for?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.48,0:21:11.04,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The money isn't that important.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.60,0:21:13.31,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's only the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.92,0:21:16.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The real problem comes after.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.35,0:21:20.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I need everyone's hope and goodwill.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.88,0:21:26.09,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that more people \Nlike this town than hate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.14,0:21:31.64,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The more people who want to \Nsave it, the more likely it is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.41,0:21:34.64,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,that we can win.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.64,0:21:37.15,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll say it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.72,0:21:39.38,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Lend your assistance to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.74,0:21:42.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,To me... And to my guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.76,0:21:48.78,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro, did you just say "guild"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.78,0:21:50.58,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,"My guild"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.61,0:21:52.58,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.05,0:21:54.70,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Then you made one?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.70,0:21:55.80,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.80,0:21:58.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, since you've invited me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.27,0:22:01.34,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's nothing to apologize for...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.82,0:22:03.13,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.13,0:22:05.87,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations, Shiro.
